Because the individual matrix elements have an invariant meaning,
it is meaningful to look at their arithmetic properties, which is
the content of the theory of the Galois action. The
basic idea is to look at the field  obtained by adjoining to the
rationals the matrix elements of all modular matrices (it is enough
to adjoin those of the generators  and ). It turns out that
the field  equals the cyclotomic field , where 
